{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "sc2-mhr-100k-001",
    "name": "StableCoin-MintHaltRestore-100K-30d",
    "description": "ACTUS Stablecoin: MINT → HALT → RESTORE Lifecycle ($100K Reserve)\n\nDemonstrates the full stablecoin mint lifecycle with $100,000 USD initial reserve:\n\n  PHASE 1 (Day 1):  Setup reserves, run CRE check, mint SUCCEEDS\n  PHASE 2 (Day 8):  Stress builds, CRE check finds underbacking, mint BLOCKED\n  PHASE 3 (Day 18): T-Bill matures, reserves recover, mint RESTORED\n\nReserve Composition (Day 1):\n  Cash:     $6,000   (bank deposits, immediate liquidity)\n  T-Bill A: $24,500  (PAM, matures Mar 15, 4-week)\n  T-Bill B: $24,500  (PAM, matures Mar 30, 8-week)\n  T-Bill C: $24,500  (PAM, matures Apr 15, 13-week)\n  T-Bill D: $24,500  (PAM, matures Apr 30, 13-week)\n  TOTAL:    $104,000  (104% backing of $100,000 supply)\n\nBehavioral Models:\n  BackingRatioModel (br_100k_01):      monitors reserve adequacy\n  RedemptionPressureModel (rp_100k_01): 609-event calibrated redemption curves\n\nACE Policy Thresholds:\n  BackingRatioPolicy:   backing >= 100% (10000 bps)\n  LiquidityRatioPolicy: liquidity >= 20% (2000 bps)\n  RiskScorePolicy:      riskScore <= 75/100\n\nContract: PAM (Principal At Maturity) representing stablecoin liability\n  notionalPrincipal = 100000 (positive for RPA role — the outstanding supply)\n  nominalInterestRate = 0.0 (stablecoins pay no interest)\n\nTargets: localhost:8082 (risk service) and localhost:8083 (sim engine)\n  For AWS: replace localhost with 34.203.247.32\n\nOpen Postman Console (Ctrl+Alt+C) before running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {"key": "actus_risk_host", "value": "localhost:8082"},
    {"key": "actus_sim_host", "value": "localhost:8083"}
  ],
